[2] Philippines: Measles outbreak, 333 dead and 22 967 cases
Date: Fri 22 Mar 2019
Source: NDRRMC [National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Center, Camp Aguinaldo, Quezon City, Philippines] Update SitRep No. 12 [transl., abridged, edited]
http://www.ndrrmc.gov.ph/attachments/article/3633/SitRep_No_12_re_Measles_Outbreak_as_of_22_March_2019_1700H.pdf


Releasing Officer: Undersecretary Ricardo B. Jalad, Executive Director, NDRRMC and Administrator, OCD

Situation overview
The Department of Health (DOH) raised the red flag for measles in other regions of Luzon, Central and Eastern Visayas on 7 Feb 2019, aside from the declaration of the National Capital Region (NCR) on 6 Jan 2019.

Effects
- A total of 333 dead were reported in Regions I, II, III, CALABARZON, MIMAROPA, V, VI, VII, VIII, X, XI, XII, CARAGA, CAR, ARMM, and NCR.
- A total of 22 967 cases of measles were reported in Regions I, II, III, CALABARZON, MIMAROPA, V, VI, VII, VIII, IX, X, XI, XII, CARAGA, BARMM, CAR, and NCR from 1 Jan 2019 to 19 Mar 2019.
- Ages of cases ranged from less than 1 month to 88 years old (median, 3 years); the most affected age-groups were 1-4 years (6551 or 29%) and less than 9 months (5826 or 25%), and the majority (12 122 or 53%) were males.
- Most of the cases were from Region IV-A (4740), NCR (4512), Region III (3,640), Region VI (1323) and Region X (1139).
- The majority (13 549 or 59%) of the cases were not vaccinated.

