[3] Macau
Date: Fri 22 Mar 2019
Source: Asia Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.asiatimes.com/2019/03/article/measles-affects-doctor-migrant-worker-in-macau/


The Macau Health Authority has confirmed 2 new cases of measles. They involve a female hospital doctor and a Nepalese migrant worker, bringing the number of confirmed cases in Macau to 8 in the first 3 months of this year [2019]. In the same period of 2018, 3 cases were recorded.

A 38-year-old Macau woman who is said to be a doctor working for the Department of Medicine in Kiang Wu Hospital in Santo Antonio, developed a fever on 14 Mar 2019 and a skin rash 5 days later. The doctor, who is now in fair condition at an isolation ward in the hospital, reportedly had contact with a patient infected with measles at work.

Another case reportedly involved a 37-year-old migrant worker from Nepal, who is said to be a groom working for Macau Jockey Club.

