[4] Macau: travel-associated
Date: Wed 20 Mar 2019
Source: Macau Business [abridged, edited]
https://protect2.fireeye.com/url?k=fcd62cf6-a0f5cb2d-fcd4d5c3-0cc47aa8c6e0-b069b0a47015a615&u=https://www.macaubusiness.com/fourth-case-of-imported-measles-in-2019-health-bureau/


A 11-month-old baby boy was infected with measles after having travelled to Switzerland, the Health Bureau (SS) announced, classifying it as an imported case. This is the 4th case of imported measles in Macau since January 2019.

According to the SS statement on Tuesday [19 Mar 2019], the baby was born in Macau but was in Switzerland during the incubation period. Pediatric Emergency Service of the Public Hospital Conde de San Januario (CHCSJ)'s laboratory results on 19 Mar 2019 confirmed that the patient was infected with measles.

He was not vaccinated against measles virus since he had not yet reached the age of vaccination, which is 1 year of age. The SS stated that the patient is currently hospitalized in the isolation nursery of the CHCSJ, still with fever but with a clinical condition considered to be normal.

