[7] Malaysia (Pahang)
Date: Tue 19 Mar 2019
Source: New Straits Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2019/03/470795/measles-cases-pahang-rise


The number of measles cases in Pahang has alarmingly increased by 200% (21 cases) this year [2019] compared with only 7 cases reported during the same period between 1 Jan and 16 Mar last year [2018]. State health director Datuk Dr Sha'ari Ngadiman said parents shunning vaccinations was a major concern as 30% of measles cases in Pahang was due to their failure to provide immunisation. He said records revealed that Kuantan was the worst affected district with 19 cases while Rompin and Temerloh had one case each.

[Byline: Siti Insyirah Tajuddin]

