[9] Texas (Collin County)
Date: Thu 21 Mar 2019
Source: Community Impact [abridged, edited]
https://communityimpact.com/dallas-fort-worth/mckinney/healthcare/2019/03/19/second-confirmed-case-of-measles-identified-in-collin-county/


A 2nd confirmed case of measles has been identified in Collin County, Texas, as of 18 Mar [2019]. As of 19 Mar [2019], this case has not yet been reported to the Texas Department of State Health Services (DSHS) but would be considered the 12th confirmed measles case in Texas this year [2019], said Chris Van Deusen, director of DSHS media relations.

The DSHS has confirmed 11 cases of measles this year as of 8 Mar 2019. Two of these cases came from Denton and Collin counties, which each had one case at the time. In 2019, Texas has seen the highest number of confirmed measles cases since 2013, according to DSHS data.

[Byline: Emily Davis]

