[17] Kenya: vaccination campaign
Date: Fri 22 Mar 2019
Source: The Star [abridged, edited]
https://www.the-star.co.ke/counties/north-eastern/2019-03-22-wajir-launches-measles-vaccination/


Wajir County in northern Kenya reported 256 cases with 4 measles-related deaths last year [2018]. Blood samples sent to Kemri tested positive. The 1st documented case was a 2-year-old boy from Danaba health centre in Wajir North. The 1st wave occurred in February 2018, while the 2nd outbreak was confirmed in September 2018. Following the 2 outbreaks in 2018, Wajir County has launched a measles vaccination drive.

Deputy governor Ahmed Mukhtar led the exercise at Qorahey grounds yesterday [21 Mar 2019]. The county government intervention includes community education, defaulter tracing and enhanced vaccination. The vaccination campaign targets 94 000 children between the ages of 6 months and 5 years. It will be done within the next 5 days across the county.

Mukhtar said the county government is committed to investing in immunisation to attain the targets and eradicate the disease. "To achieve this, we have established 102 immunisation centres out of the 115 operational facilities," Mukhtar said, adding that plans are underway to provide equipment in the remaining facilities to bridge the access gap.

